'''Edith Vernick''' was an American [[animator]], hired by the [[Fleischer Studios]] in the mid-1920s and became the In between Department Supervisor. Her animation work is uncredited on ''The Fresh Vegetable Mystery'' from 1939.  Although [[Lillian Friedman Astor]] is generally considered the first female American animator, Vernick's employment at the Fleischer Studios preceded Friedman's.

