{{Infobox book | name = Harnessing the Power of Wisdom: From Data to Wisdom | image = Cover photo of Harnessing the Power of Wisdom, From Data to Wisdom.jpg | alt = Harnessing the Power of Wisdom: From Data to Wisdom | caption = First edition cover | author = [[Andrew Targowski]] | country = United States | language = English | subject = [[Philosophy]] | publisher = [[Nova Science Publishers]] | release_date = 2013 | media_type = Print ([[Hardcover]]) | pages = 169 | isbn = 978-1-62618-890-7 }}
'''''Harnessing The Power Of Wisdom: From Data to Wisdom''''' is a philosophical book by [[Andrew Targowski]] that discusses the concept and status of wisdom in modern society.
==Summary== In the book Targowski defines wisdom as good judgement and choice and also states that wisdom can be taught. He goes on to say that wisdom is one portion of the cognitive units that create the Semantic Ladder: Data, Information, Concept, Knowledge, and Wisdom. Targowski also gives his reasons as to why civilization is, as a whole, further behind than it was in [[Ancient Greece|Greek]] times on a philosophical level. He opines that even with the advances in the realm of [[Information Technology]] (IT), society remains unable to convert the information at its fingertips into the ultimate form of knowledge and wisdom. This book besides scientific synthesis of wisdom covers also the “art of living” and the decline in human ability to achieve its greatest potential as a global community.
==Reception== ''Biocosmology'' gave ''Harnessing the Power of Wisdom'' a positive review, stating that it was "a remarkable wise contribution to the contemporary cultural world, forming an interdisciplinary theory of wisdom and conception of the wise Integralist civilization. Substantially, this is a significant step towards the integral organization of contemporary social and cultural life, and a valuable piece of information of the integrally organizing essence."<ref>{{cite journal|last1=KHROUTSKI|first1=Konstantin S.|title=Harnessing the Power of Wisdom (review)|journal=Biocosmology|date=Winter–Spring 2014|volume=4|issue=1-2|url=https://b0e97027-a-62cb3a1a-s-sites.googlegroups.com/site/biocosmologyneoaristotelism/home/1-1/91.Khroutski.pdf?attachauth=ANoY7co65XKmU1AoJK3kiSTL_ce8HaUjsJ5FhGmXWr6GPU81tWDAXkj6SPHqqRCBBzNDUIMtQoc11hpYRG4EgVWz6S2Rfj7UBSFMH9UaGOw67snlNDvvFYThNoehQyACpjNld8SIK4cVeflCZvKQkCmuIOiQyUf-G2sT5-MoBl5VZ7GGGBXYXOY656Eb97a4KUf2ycwo1pfL0hVncVPTOyjCTpKMKBf7b9YxOO40J8YsbQjEIZ09bPt08t-oZV3QakbrCT4TUIhX&attredirects=0|accessdate=2 July 2015}}</ref> ''Dialogue and Universalism'' also praised the work and made it one of the main focuses of one of their 2014 issues where they brought in 8 writers to reflect on the work.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Kato|first1=Hisanori|title=A Way to Wisdom|journal=Dialogue and Universalism|date=2014|volume=24|issue=2|pages=222–223|doi=10.5840/du201424242|url=http://www.pdcnet.org/pdc/bvdb.nsf/purchase?openform&fp=du&id=du_2014_0024_0002_0222_0223|accessdate=2 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=III. WISDOM. DISCUSSION ABOUT ANDREW TARGOWSKI’S BOOK: HARNESSING THE POWER OF WISDOM: FROM DATA TO WISDOM|journal=Dialogue and Universalism|date=2014|issue=2|url=http://dialogueanduniversalism.eu/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/2014-2.pdf|accessdate=2 July 2015}}</ref>
